SUMMARY:Nel Begley & Friends: Jazz at The Half Moon Herne Hill
LOCATION:The Half Moon, 10 Half Moon Lane, SE24 9HU
DESCRIPTION:Doors open 30mins before the performance.

Opening the Herne Hill Music Festival is South London-based jazz singer and songwriter Nel Begley. A graduate of both Leeds Conservatoire and Guildhall School of Music & Drama, Nel blends classic jazz influences with a contemporary edge, delivering soulful melodies and heartfelt lyrics that captivate audiences.

 Honey Boulton (one of London___s premier guitarists and banjoists), the remarkably versatile Harry Brunt on saxophone and on Bass, her partner in both music and life, Luke Fowler.

Nel will be launching her brand-new album ___Small Flame___. Available now on Bandcamp, signed copies of the CD will also be available on the night.
